ratings.rComments: Followed Randy for my freshmen year and learned a lot. Homework is good material for study as well as the worksheets he assigned in discussions. He does before class exercising with question regarding material learned before but I can't get up that early... Lecture is really useful and try to put effort in the study.

Calc 2 is notoriously hard,but Randy made it very manageable. The TAs I had were phenomenal and without them I wouldn't have passed. While at times it seemed like I was in way over my head, he assigns lots of problems (both homework and practice) and is very forgiving in his grading policies.

Good professor, lectures are super helpful! He tells you exactly what each problem on the test will be on however, the tests are tough. Fair grading policy ( doesn't curve but will replace one midterm with the final.) You can tell he wants you to learn not just get a grade. Hard class but I actually learned calculus.
I liked him
Does not give partial credit which sucks. while you know the types of questions that will be on the test, he makes them extremely difficult. I never missed a class, and it was still super challenging

If you really want to LEARN Calculus, take Randy's class. He's an excellent instructor, and designs his class such that if you work hard, you'll get a good grade. So if you are up for the challenge and are willing to work hard, you'll do well and have a great understanding of Calculus.

He knows his stuff, but he's kinda intimidating. He doesn't always go over what you're expected to know. He's really funny though and clearly intelligent.  I really tried and still didn't do well though.
Seriously, do not take his class. Tests are tough,and he is a harsh grader.

Brilliant lecturer. Gave me new perspective on a lot of things, often explained how things being taught were used in daily life. Tells exactly what is going to be on the exam, does not test unnecessary stuff. Book use minimal to none. Actually solving webassign helps a lot. Exams are challenging, but interesting and manageable. I loved his class!

Even through I didn't get an awesome grade, Professor McCarthy is a great math professor. Lectures are amazing, go to them! He's very clear and doesn't over complicate things. Tests are pretty hard, but he tells you what's on them! He has a grade replacement policy and overall is a fair grader. Definitely recommend.

Lectures are helpful because he goes over some questions that will likely be tested on. Lots of what he says will be unclear unless you pre read the section  he is going over. With this class its all on you to understand the material. Use the tutoring its free. Use the past exams and the outlines of the test he gives before the exam.

The lectures are barely useful and he spends 20 minutes on theorems in order to help you understand that just end up confusing you and wasting class time. He attempts to give extra help with tutoring and practice tests but with 1 TA for 20 students and no answer key, who does this really help? Also picks trick questions for exams on purpose.

Professor McCarthy loves to add online assignments with just a couples days notice (a huge inconvenience when trying to deal with an engineering workload), his tests and assignments are rather loosely based around what he actually teaches during lectures, and he's a very harsh grader. He also offers almost no material to prepare for exams.
Brilliant Class

He's a pretty great teacher. I took the engineering section of calc 2 first semster and dropped it quickly. But when i took his class in the spring, i did awesome in it and he loves it if you ask him questions after class and in office hours. He was so much easier to understand, I wish he taught all my math classes.

He's nice in the grading since he provides students bonus and replacement for the lowest exam score. His teaching is not bad but I have to learn things by myself after class. His exam is not very easy though. But still, thanks to the bonus and replacement he gives, I did very well in math  231.

Great teacher, loves what he does. You have to work hard to learn the material, but he tells you EXACTLY what you need to know for exams, so if you put the time in you'll get a good grade. He's very helpful and set up a tutoring service run by TA's, so if you want to succeed the resources are there for you to succeed. Great guy and great teacher

probably the best calculus professor here. strongly recommend taking his classes. calc is obviously not an easy class and it requires a lot of work but he sets all the students up for success. tells you what is going to be on every test and replaces one test grade with final.

Really great professor!Strongly advice to take Calc with him. Work hard to make students understand and always patient to explain.Tell you exactly what will be on the exam. Go to the lectures, pay attention and you will be fine. Very high value past exams. Hard homework on webassign, not closely related, but provide answers right away. Easy quiz.
Amazing teacher- funny and intelligent.

lectures make you understand what you're doing spatially and mathematically.evaluations are difficult if you aren't naturally a math genius. he tells you what types of problems will be on them which helps though. don't buy the book, nobody opens it even once. discussion section didn't help, it's just very hard group worksheets.TA's didn't help much

I do think McCarthy is a good professor. I like the way he teaches. He tells us what's on the exam. Though the questions are a little bit tricky, if you go to the lecture every time and prepare exactly as the question type, you'll be fine. Going to the lecture is important!!! He explains very well and clearly and can save you plenty of time!

Not only does he belittle to students, but he tries to do theorems the long way with the idea that he's making us "think", when in reality he's actually killing 15 minutes doing archaic junk that helps nobody. Telling us what's on the exam is helpful, but it feels like in order to compensate for that he has to include trick questions.

He is a great teacher, he explains things in a clear manner, tells you what will be on the test. He also keeps lecture interesting. Keep in mind that teaching math is hard, therefore this is a big plus.
Very helpful.
Tell's you exactly what's going to be on the exam!

Tells you EXACTLY what questions are going to be on the exams. Very helpful! His exams are difficult and some of the TAs grade it harshly, but my advice - do and practice homework problems and know some basic trigonometry as the final from last semester had a lot of algebra on it, especially trig.

You can tell from the way he proves things that he is a GENIUS! And that is the problem...he's a genius. He teaches the way that he understands it rather than the way students would think about it. But he helped students. His exams are pretty difficult, especially last semester's final. Practice homework problems and know that unit circle for trig!

Randy is awesome, I had him for calc 1, and again for calc 2 next semester and I couldnt be more happy with that. He tells you exactly what is going to be on the tests, gives you answers to HW, and works with you to make sure you get best grade possible. If it puts things in perspective, I got a 3 on the AP but an A in his class. Not that he's easy

I had him for Calc 221 and I'm taking his 231 class too. I thought his lectures were perfectly clear, and I went to office hours which was a huge help. Discussion sections suck though, it's just group work the whole time. The homework is super easy- it tells you all the right answers so you can just get a 100% on every assignment. I reccomend him!
This course is extremely easy. All the work sheets and homework will prepare for the exams well. And he is a really funny man, who always telling a joke on lecture. nice guy!

He is a great professor. You can tell he likes math. A lot. He has high expectations for the class, which is why some of his exams are difficult. He makes sure you know the exact type of problem for every problem on the test. Attend lectures and study. Not a terribly hard A.

Easy exams. Just do the homework and worksheets they will prepare you for his exams. Go to lecture he will tell what is on the test and it will be on there just reworded!! If you need help go to office hours he will help you.

He was funny and interesting in lecture, although they werent helpful. Worksheets and quizzes in discussion weren't helpful either. I went to my TA's office hours a lot and that helped sometimes but I was always unprepared for the difficulty of his tests. Said he wouldn't curve, but he did. Final was easy cause I studied past tests. very Hard!

There isn't much positive to say about his class. His lectures DO NOT prepare you for tests. The textbook doesn't either. I can honestly say I wasted several hours a day studying from  lecture notes and the textbook just to struggle excessively on the test. Tests are exponentially more difficult than quizzes, worksheets, and textbook work.

Like to joke around. Told us what was on the exams the class right before them. Exams were reasonable and usually curved. Lots of extra credit opportunities. HW was online and if you got the wrong answer, the right answer would pop up. Short quiz every Thursday. He averages out your worst hour exam grade if you do well on Final exam.

Tough honors class, lots of proofs, but had a solid curve.  Randy's explanations aren't very helpful or intuitive, but it was rewarding to finally understand concepts.  Randy is an enthusiastic guy though, especially w.r.t. topology.

Hard class. Discussion did not help at all. Lectures were confusing so ended up teaching myself the material. Curve was much needed. TA office hours helped but professor made me feel stupid at his office hours. Do not recommend.

Pretty straightforward calc class. His lectures are sometimes confusing, and he often has trouble answering questions from students. The tests were pretty brutal. However, he was pretty reasonable on grades, and always curved things pretty favorably.
Handwriting was messy and hard to read
Awesome teacher!  Great guy and supremely helpful. :)

Randy does make his class very hard. But his lectures are fairly clear, and he tells you more or less exactly what will be on the tests. The tests are difficult and long still. If you do your homework and go to class you should be fine.
Great class to enhance your texting skills

I thought that he was a great professor and very clear. He did not put anything on the exams that weren't expected and told you exactly what would be on the exams. If you go to lecture, do the homework, and go to lecture then you will do well.

Horrid professor! His exams are really long and not only does he not give you enough time but he also makes the next exams longer. Worst of all you never know what to write on the exam for full credit. Overall awful professor! Avoid at all cost!
Absolutely horrid teacher. Gives you too little time for exams and then makes the next ones even longer. Worst of all you never know what he expects you to write on the exam for full credit.

MATH 406 was by far one of the worst classes I have ever took. This professor took a course, which everyone thought would be a walk in the park and turned it into a one of the hardest courses I have ever taken. If you think that math 406 with Randy is going to be easy think again. I received my lowest grade from this guy out of all my classes.

Incredibly fun for a math professor. Very reasonable on grading procedures, fairly laid back. I'd take a math class from him over any other math professor I have had...you have to take what you can get in the math department.
